# Project Conventions

## NestJS API (`apps/api/`)

### Module Structure
- One module per domain: `auth/`, `kb/`, `skill/`, `neo4j/`, `search/`, `cache/`
- Each module: `*.module.ts`, `*.service.ts`, `*.controller.ts`, `*.dto.ts`
- Shared modules (`Neo4jModule`, `CacheModule`, `SearchModule`) are `@Global()`
- Guards implement `CanActivate`; register global guard via `APP_GUARD`

### Naming
- Files: kebab-case (`api-key.guard.ts`, `kb.service.ts`)
- Classes: PascalCase matching file (`ApiKeyGuard`, `KbService`)
- DTOs: `VerbNounDto` pattern (`PushSolutionDto`, `PublishSkillDto`)

### Guards & Auth
- `MasterGuard`: validates `x-master-password` header for admin endpoints
- `ApiKeyGuard`: validates `x-api-key` header via bcrypt comparison
- Apply with `@UseGuards(GuardClass)` on controller or method

### Validation
- All DTOs use `class-validator` decorators (`@IsString()`, `@IsOptional()`)
- Global `ValidationPipe` with `whitelist: true, transform: true`

### Error Handling
- Throw NestJS `HttpException` subclasses (`NotFoundException`, `UnauthorizedException`)
- Never expose internal errors to client; log and rethrow generic

## Neo4j / Cypher

### Query Rules
- ALWAYS use parameterized queries: `$variableName`, never string interpolation
- MERGE for idempotent operations (creating nodes that may exist)
- `ON CREATE SET` must come before `SET` after MERGE
- Use `neo4j.int()` for all integer parameters (SKIP, LIMIT)
- Always DETACH DELETE (removes relationships automatically)

### Constraints
- ALL constraints created in `Neo4jService.onModuleInit()` — never in other services
- Pattern: `CREATE CONSTRAINT name IF NOT EXISTS FOR (n:Label) REQUIRE n.prop IS UNIQUE`

### Session Management
- Open session per query, close immediately after
- Never hold sessions across async boundaries
- Use `session.run()` directly, not transactions, unless multi-statement atomicity needed

## Bun CLI (`packages/cli/`)

### Command Structure
- Commander program with subcommand groups: `kb` (search/push/list/get), skill verbs (install/publish/compose)
- Options: `--flag value` pattern, use `.option()` with description
- Action handlers: async, wrap in try/catch with `ora` spinner

### Output
- `ora` for async operations (start before, succeed/fail after)
- `chalk` for colors: green=success, red=error, dim=secondary info
- Tables for list output; truncate long content with ellipsis

### Config
- `conf` package stores at `~/.skill-cli/config.json`
- Keys: `hub_url`, `api_key`, `default_project`, `skills_dir`
- Never hardcode URLs or credentials

## Docker Compose

### Port Mapping
- Document why non-standard host ports: `3456:3000` (avoid VPS conflicts)
- Internal ports stay standard (containers talk on default ports)
- Comment each port mapping

### Volumes
- Named volumes for persistence (data survives container recreation)
- `:ro` suffix for read-only mounts (nginx.conf, certs)

### Environment
- `.env` file for secrets (gitignored)
- `.env.example` committed with placeholder values
- `env_file: .env` in service definition
